# 🚀 Hybrid Breakthrough — Implementation Plan

## Goal
Break the **0.954 Public LB** ceiling by combining 4 orthogonal model families that attack redundancy (correlation 0.999) from different angles.

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[630k Train Data] --> B[Feature Engineering]
    B --> C1[GBDT Trio: XGB+LGBM+CAT]
    B --> C2[Zone-RF: 4-Zone Regime]
    B --> C3[MLP Neural Network]
    B --> C4[UCI Stats Enrichment]
    C1 --> D[OOF Stacking]
    C2 --> D
    C3 --> D
    C4 --> D
    D --> E[LR Meta-Learner]
    E --> F[Final Submission]
```

## Components

### 1. Zone-RF (Regime Decomposition)
- Split patients into 4 zones: `vessels_fluro` × `thallium`
- Train separate RF per zone with tailored depth
- Expected correlation with GBDT: **~0.85** (LOW!)

### 2. UCI Target Statistics
- Extract `mean(target)` per [(cp, sex, thal)](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/heart_pipeline_v10_14_sota.py#62-80) from original 270 UCI rows
- Inject as 3 new features into synthetic data
- Provides real-world signal missing from synthetic generation

### 3. MLP Neural Network
- `sklearn.neural_network.MLPClassifier(256, 128)`
- Learns non-axis-aligned interactions
- Expected correlation with GBDT: **~0.88** (LOW!)

### 4. GBDT Trio (Baseline)
- XGB + LGBM + CAT, all features, 5-fold CV
- Our proven 0.95387 anchor

### 5. LR Meta-Learner (Stacking)
- `LogisticRegression` on 5 OOF vectors (XGB, LGBM, CAT, Zone-RF, MLP)
- Final calibrated prediction

## Verification
- OOF must be in 0.955–0.960 range (NOT above 0.960)
- Submit to Kaggle, target LB > 0.954
- ProcessGuard checks all cross-correlations < 0.95
